.SH hsh

.SH NAME
hsh - simple shell program

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh [command] [argument]
for interactive mode and
.B echo "[command] [argument]" | ./hsh
for non-interactive mode.

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple command-line interface used to interact with an operating system, allowing users to execute commands and run scripts.

The shell supports executing commands with or without specifying their full paths.

hsh uses the PATH environment variable to search for commands if the command is not a full path.

.SH OPTIONS
None.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns 0 on success and non-zero on failure.

